    "body": "Hi @zcbenz \nEven call `setApplicationMenu` again also doesn't work.\nFor example:\n\n``` javascript\n\nvar app = require('electron').app,\n    Menu = require('electron').Menu,\n    BrowserWindow = require('electron').BrowserWindow;\n\nvar mainWindow = null;\n\napp.on('ready', function() {\n  mainWindow = new BrowserWindow({ width: 600, height: 400 })\n  var m = Menu.buildFromTemplate([{\n    label: 'test',\n    submenu: [{label: 'test-test'}]\n  }, {\n    label: 'hello',\n    submenu: [{label: 'hello-test'}]\n  }]);\n\n  m.items[1].submenu.items[0].label = 'hello-hello';\n  console.log(m.items[1].submenu);\n\n  mainWindow.setMenu(m);\n  Menu.setApplicationMenu(m);\n});\n\n```\n\nIn console you can see label is changed to 'hello-hello', but the menu shown is still 'hello-test'\nIs it by design?\n\nThanks\n"
